  491|       |            // Previously this slot was "raw bytes verbatim" which produces
  492|       |            // a syntactically-invalid params body 99% of the time and
  493|       |            // dies at envelope-level `serde_json::from_str::<Request>`
  494|       |            // instead of reaching the per-method `Params::parse::<T>`
  495|       |            // surface. By selecting a template based on the method name,
  496|       |            // we hand `Params::parse` a *type-shaped* body so the
  497|       |            // per-method decoder runs — that's the actual surface where
  498|       |            // per-method input-parsing panics live.
  499|       |            //
  500|       |            // The remaining fuzz bytes feed the template fields, so
  501|       |            // libFuzzer can mutate around the type shape (e.g. flip a
  502|       |            // bool, twiddle a number, lengthen a hex string) and reach
  503|       |            // both the success path and the per-field rejection paths.
  504|  1.14k|            build_method_param_template(method, payload)
  505|       |        }
  506|       |    };
